description:
Marathons and Ironmans are two of the most challenging athletic endeavours on the planet, the ultimate test of strength and endurance.

They're considered by most as barely possible, but not for the Team Hoyt father-son duo. This duo was so special because Rick, the son, was born with cerebral palsy and was a quadriplegic. And so, his father, Dick, pushed and pulled him in specialised wheelchairs, bikes, and boats.

They completed over 1,000 races and were immensely devoted to each other as ever, inspiring millions worldwide with their trademark motto, "Yes, you can." This is one of the greatest love stories of all time. A father who climbs mountains, runs marathons, travels to the ends of the earth to give his son a better life, a life that transcends the limitations of his body. This story shows that through perseverance and determination, love conquers all.

In Memory of...
– Dick Hoyt: June 1, 1940 – March 17, 2021
– Rick Hoyt: January 10, 1962 – May 22, 2023
